<item>
            <title>[SUREFIRE-1357] PING scheduler kills JVM in debug mode</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SUREFIRE-1357</link>
                <project id="12317927" key="SUREFIRE">Maven Surefire (Moved to GitHub Issues)</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;This issue was found during second Vote of Version 2.20.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Configuration parameter &lt;tt&gt;debugForkedProcess=true&lt;/tt&gt; kills the JVM because all threads are disabled for scheduling purposes and PING scheduler suggested killing JVM when developer stepped into a break point after 20 seconds.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The dump file contains error&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;tt&gt;Corrupted stdin stream in forked JVM 1. Stream &apos;Listening for transport dt_socket at address: 5005&apos;.&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
